      "q": "Summit Roasters estimates this long-run average cost schedule. 1,000 units: average cost $100 2,000 units: average cost $76 4,000 units: average cost $62 8,000 units: average cost $64 What is the minimum efficient scale?",
      "options": [
        "8,000 units, because the largest plant always has the lowest efficient scale",
        "4,000 units, the smallest output level where the lowest average cost is reached",
        "1,000 units, because producing fewer units avoids coordination cost",
        "It cannot be identified because minimum efficient scale uses marginal revenue, not average cost"
      ],
